04/06/2003
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The BiH presidency forwarded the reciprocal agreement with the United States barring citizens from extradition to the International Criminal Court to parliament Tuesday (3 June).
Parliamentary debates on the issue are scheduled for Friday, according to the local news agency SRNA.
The parliament is expected to ratify the agreement by the end of the month.
Also Tuesday, the BiH Parliament's House of Representatives approved amendments to the law on radio and television.
The change allows direct broadcasting of the sessions of the two parliamentary chambers in the federation.
In addition to the amendments, parliamentarians agreed to launch further discussions about the national radio and TV as soon as possible.
(Dnevni Avaz - 04/06/03;
SRNA, BBC - 03/06/03)
